ZH: 当我唱歌的时候，朋友总是在一旁帮腔。
EN: When I sing, my friends always join in chorus.

ZH: 她以一种温柔的方式在演唱会上给我帮腔。
EN: She supports me on stage in a tender way.

ZH: 每次我在阅读时，他都会帮腔解释生词。
EN: Whenever I read, he helps me explain new words.

ZH: 我需要一个伴奏者来帮腔我的歌曲表演。
EN: I need an accompanist to support my song performance.

ZH: 他经常在我需要帮助的时候无私地帮腔。
EN: He selflessly supports me whenever I need help.

ZH: 她是我的忠实听众，总是在听我唱歌时帮腔。
EN: She is my loyal listener, always joining in when I sing.

ZH: 当我无法唱高音时，他会帮腔出来弥补。
EN: When I can't hit the high notes, he jumps in and compensates.

ZH: 我很感激她每次都愿意帮腔我在舞台上的表演。
EN: I am grateful for her willingness to support my stage performances.

ZH: 无论何时，他都在我身边帮腔我所表达的观点。
EN: He is always there to support the viewpoints I express.

ZH: 她是我音乐之路上最好的帮腔之一。
EN: She is one of the best supporters on my musical journey.

ZH: 我以一种谦虚的态度接受他给予我的帮腔。
EN: I humbly accept the support he offers me.

ZH: 在这个关键时刻，他是我最可靠的帮腔伙伴。
EN: At this crucial moment, he is my most reliable supporting partner.

ZH: 她只是在表达自己观点时给予我帮腔而已。
EN: She simply joins in as a supporting voice when expressing her opinions.

ZH: 这个演讲需要一个帮腔者来增强效果。
EN: This speech needs a supporting voice to enhance the effect.

ZH: 他的帮腔让我更加自信地发表演讲。
EN: His supporting voice gives me more confidence in delivering the speech.

ZH: 老师在课堂上会帮腔学生们的讨论和互动。
EN: The teacher supports student discussions and interactions in the classroom.

ZH: 我愿意成为你的帮腔者，支持你的决定。
EN: I am willing to be your supporting voice and support your decisions.

ZH: 在这个项目中，我会尽力成为你的帮腔。
EN: In this project, I will do my best to be your supporting voice.

ZH: 老板希望我能帮腔他的新战略。
EN: The boss wants me to support his new strategy.

ZH: 我的音乐合作伙伴总是在我需要时无条件地帮腔我。
EN: My music partner always unconditionally supports me when I need it.
